.Dd Aug 15, 2025
.Dt gufi_trace2index
.Os Linux
.Sh NAME
.Nm gufi_trace2index
.Nd converts a GUFI trace file into a GUFI index
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op options
input_file
output_dir

.Sh DESCRIPTION
Use the trace file generated by gufi_dir2trace to generate a GUFI index.

.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width -indent
.It Fl h
help
.It Fl H
show assigned input values (debugging)
.It Fl n\ <threads>
number of threads
.It Fl d\ <delim>
delimiter (one char)  [use 'x' for 0x1E]
.It input_file
parse this trace file to produce the GUFI index
.It output_dir
build GUFI index here
.El

.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Bl -tag -width -indent
.It EXIT_SUCCESS or EXIT_FAILURE
.El

.Pp
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width -compact
.It gufi_trace2index
.El

.Sh NOTES
.Nm
was once part of the executable "bfwi".

\# .Sh BUGS
\# .Sh EXAMPLE

.Sh FLOW
 input file is opened
 threads are started
 A thread is started to scout out directory entries in the input file and populate the work queues with them

 loop assigning work (directories) from queue to threads
   The output directory of this work item is created.
   Create a database file in the directory.
   The trace is read and converted to entries in the database.
   Close the database file
 end

.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr gufi_dir2index 1 ,
.Xr gufi_dir2trace 1
